You could actually just say "this is my GPS
utility app."

00:27:07.210 --> 00:27:08.210
&gt;&gt;Reto: Yeah.

00:27:08.210 --> 00:27:09.210
Absolutely.

00:27:09.210 --> 00:27:12.509
And as far as that goes, that may then control
how you decide to structure your navigation.

00:27:12.509 --> 00:27:16.669
Cause I think fundamentally even more important
than the graphics element, which I think,

00:27:16.669 --> 00:27:20.679
I'm quite sure a lot of people are gonna disagree
with us and be like "No, I love the old school

00:27:20.679 --> 00:27:21.679
stuff."

00:27:21.679 --> 00:27:22.679
&gt;&gt;Trevor: Its' always subjective.

00:27:22.679 --> 00:27:23.679
&gt;&gt;Reto: Exactly.

00:27:23.679 --> 00:27:26.480
But I think much more important than that
is sorting out the navigation.

00:27:26.480 --> 00:27:27.779
Make it much clearer.

00:27:27.779 --> 00:27:29.009
Where you are in the app.

00:27:29.009 --> 00:27:30.669
How to move to different parts of it.

00:27:30.669 --> 00:27:31.830
And make everything work together.

00:27:31.830 --> 00:27:35.169
And I think figuring out what is the key purpose.

00:27:35.169 --> 00:27:38.539
I talked a little bit about this during my
IO session this year.

00:27:38.539 --> 00:27:40.139
But, what is the focus.

00:27:40.139 --> 00:27:43.539
What is the thing that you want people to
associate your app with?

00:27:43.539 --> 00:27:47.619
Is it, oh yea, I wanna check to see what the
GPS quality is?

00:27:47.619 --> 00:27:51.580
So I'm gonna use GPS test and fire it up and
see exactly how many satellites are in view

00:27:51.580 --> 00:27:53.070
and what the accuracy is?

00:27:53.070 --> 00:27:57.320
Or do you want it to be like OK, I'm going
for a hike or I'm going fishing and I wanna

00:27:57.320 --> 00:28:00.859
be able to mark down the best fishing spots
and the best hiking trails?

00:28:00.859 --> 00:28:04.149
And so I'm gonna use GPS test navigation to
do that.

00:28:04.149 --> 00:28:06.499
